MEAL SERVICE UPDATE: The U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) and the Illinois State Board of Education recently announced the extension of the free summer food service program for children ages 18 and under. District 155 will now provide free grab-and-go breakfast and lunch meals for children who live in District 155 boundaries, regardless of free/reduced lunch status.

üçé Meals will be available for pick-up at Crystal Lake Central High School, located at 45 W. Franklin Ave. in Crystal Lake (field house entrance off Walkup).
üçé Food will be provided Monday through Friday, from 8:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.
üçé Children can receive breakfast and lunch for up to three days per pickup.

Questions regarding meal service can be directed to distmail@d155.org.

District administration presented the TENTATIVE Return to School Plan at the Strategic Planning Committee Meeting on Tuesday night. We apologize for the technical difficulties and limitations in viewing the meeting live. We paid Zoom to increase our capacity to 10,000 attendees and tested the system multiple times prior to the meeting. We made several attempts to troubleshoot the issue and were unsuccessful. We have contacted Zoom so we do not run into this issue in the future. We were able to capture a recording of the meeting and it‚Äôs available HERE: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qJ2GA396ys0&feature=youtu.be&t=1

Please be advised that this recording, district administration's presentation, and the TENTATIVE Return to School Plan was sent to all staff and families and is posted on our website at d155.org.

#THANKFULTHURSDAY: We're back again to recognize the D155 alumni who are responding to the COVID-19 crisis and say THANK YOU for their efforts to keep us all safe! And thank you to our community for continuing to nominate these incredible graduates!

üè•Allie Flowers graduated from Crystal Lake Central High School and is an ICU nurse at Rush University Medical Center in Chicago.
üè•Emma Gaulke is a Cary-Grove High School graduate working as a nurse in the NICU at the Children's Hospital of Denver in Colorado.
üè•Caitlin Schumacher Peters graduated from Crystal Lake South High School and is now a Speech Pathologist at St. Luke's South Hospital in Overland Park, KS.
üè•Abby Vohaska, a Prairie Ridge High School graduate, is working in Anchorage, Alaska as a nurse in the Neonatal ICU at Providence Hospital.

If you know more D155 alumni involved in the response to COVID-19, please send their name and photo to distmail@d155.org. Stay safe and stay healthy!

üè•Courtney Kreston graduated from Crystal Lake South High School in 2016 and is now working as a nurse at the Mayo Clinic in Rochester, MN.
üè• Denise McDaniel is another CLC graduate currently working as a nurse at Ann & Robert H. Lurie Children's Hospital of Chicago.

If you know more D155 alumni involved in the response to COVID-19, comment down below or let us know at distmail@d155.org. Stay safe and stay healthy!
